# SurfDoc Extension Test

This file exercises all major syntax features for visual verification.

## Core Blocks

::callout[type=info title="Welcome"]
This is an **info callout** with markdown inside.
It should highlight the `::callout` opener, the attributes, and the `::` closer.
::

::callout[type=warning]
A warning without a custom title.
::

::decision[status=closed date=2026-02-22 owner="Brady"]
**Rust for everything** — one language across server, CLI, parser, browser, mobile core.
::

::summary
This document tests syntax highlighting for the SurfDoc VS Code extension.
All 37+ block types, front matter, attributes, nesting, and inline extensions.
::

